modules.description: Provides functions to create and manage publish/subscribe channels, allowing multiple streams to receive updates from a single source. Operates on 'a input and Lwt_stream.t types, enabling asynchronous data propagation. Used to coordinate real-time updates between independent components in event-driven systems.

Provides functions to manage event propagation through a publish/subscribe system using Lwt streams. It works with input objects that emit values and stream endpoints that receive them, along with stopper tokens to manage client lifecycles. Clients can track events from a specific input or create isolated fake streams for testing.
